# Skill: Source Discovery

## Purpose

Identify relevant public sources related to **agentic coding ecosystems**, including programming languages, frameworks, benchmarks, and ecosystem maturity signals.

This skill is responsible for building and expanding the project's **source registry**, which later analysis tasks will use.

---

## When to Use

Use this skill when the project needs to:

- discover new research sources
- identify benchmark reports
- locate framework updates
- expand the literature dataset

---

## Inputs

- project focus: agentic coding maturity
- target languages (ABAP, Python, JavaScript, Java, Go, C#)
- target frameworks (Antigravity, LangChain, AutoGen, SAP Joule, ReAct)
- research keywords

---

## Process

1. Search for sources related to the project focus.
2. Prioritize high-signal sources such as:

   - research papers
   - engineering blog posts
   - benchmark reports
   - framework documentation

3. Avoid low-quality or irrelevant sources.
4. Record metadata for each discovered source.

---

## Output

Each discovered source should include:

- title
- url
- source_type
- date
- relevance_note

Example output:

title: SAP’s ABAP-1 Loses Every ABAP Benchmark  
url: https://example.com/article  
source_type: blog  
date: 2025-XX-XX  
relevance_note: Discusses benchmark comparisons between ABAP agents and other ecosystems.

---

## Notes

The objective is to build a **high-quality source registry**, not to scrape large amounts of content.

Focus on relevance, credibility, and ecosystem signal strength.